{# Case time-sensitivity / statute-of-limitations advisory (v0.35).

   LEGAL INFORMATION, NOT LEGAL ADVICE. Two clocks:
     1. Practical — how long ago funds reached each exchange (freeze window).
        Computed from on-chain timestamps; no legal claim.
     2. Legal — criminal/civil limitation periods, each with a REAL statutory
        citation, sourced from recupero.legal.limitations. Unknown
        jurisdictions and compound periods resolve to "confirm with counsel"
        rather than a guessed date.

   The approximate runout dates ASSUME the clock started on the incident date;
   accrual / tolling / the discovery rule (counsel's call) can move them.

   Context: `ts` (recupero.legal.time_sensitivity.TimeSensitivity),
   `case_id`, `generated_at`.
#}<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Case Time-Sensitivity Advisory — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="background:#1e3a8a;color:#fff;padding:.75rem 1rem;border-radius:6px;margin:0 0 1rem;font-weight:600;line-height:1.4">
    ⚖ LEGAL INFORMATION — NOT LEGAL ADVICE. This advisory flags time limits that
    may affect recovery so they are not missed. It is general information, not a
    legal opinion. Whether any period below governs this matter — and the exact
    date it runs — depends on the applicable law, when the claim accrued, and any
    tolling. Confirm everything here with licensed counsel in the relevant
    jurisdiction before relying on it.
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Time-Sensitivity Advisory</div>
    <h1>Acting Before the Clock Runs</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Recovery of misappropriated digital assets is time-sensitive on two fronts:
      a <strong>practical</strong> window (funds can leave an exchange within
      minutes) and a <strong>legal</strong> window (criminal and civil limitation
      periods bar action once they run). This advisory summarises both for
      {{ ts.victim_name }}.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Number</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id or "—" }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Victim Jurisdiction</dt>
      <dd>{{ ts.jurisdiction_raw or "not specified" }}<span class="secondary">{% if ts.jurisdiction_canonical %}recognized as {{ ts.jurisdiction_canonical }}{% else %}not matched to a seeded reference — confirm with counsel{% endif %}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Incident Date</dt>
      <dd>{{ ts.incident_date or "—" }}{% if ts.days_since_incident is not none %}<span class="secondary">{{ ts.days_since_incident }} day(s) ago</span>{% endif %}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>As Of</dt>
      <dd>{{ ts.as_of }}</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<section class="content">

<h2>1. Practical Clock — Exchange Freeze Window</h2>
{% if ts.exchange_clocks %}
<p>
Stolen funds were traced into the deposit address(es) of the exchange(s) below.
An administrative freeze is most realistic the sooner it is requested — every
day widens the window in which funds can be withdrawn.
</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Exchange</th>
      <th>Funds first arrived</th>
      <th class="amount">Days ago</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for c in ts.exchange_clocks %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ c.exchange }}</td>
      <td>{% if c.first_flow_at %}{{ c.first_flow_at[:10] }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{% if c.days_since_first_flow is not none %}{{ c.days_since_first_flow }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p class="secondary">
The asset-freeze request deliverable (per exchange) is the action that acts on
this window. Send it through the exchange's confirmed law-enforcement channel.
</p>
{% else %}
<p>
No exchange deposits were identified in the documented flow, so no exchange
freeze-window clock is shown. If funds remain at an exchange, that exchange's
clock is the most urgent.
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>2. Legal Clock — Limitation Periods</h2>
{% if ts.confirm_with_counsel and not ts.limitation_clocks %}
<div style="background:#7c2d12;color:#fff;padding:.75rem 1rem;border-radius:6px;margin:.5rem 0;font-weight:600;line-height:1.4">
  No verified limitation reference is on file for
  {{ ts.jurisdiction_raw or "this jurisdiction" }}. Recupero does not assert a
  period it cannot cite. Confirm the applicable criminal and civil limitation
  periods — and their accrual / tolling rules — with licensed counsel in the
  relevant jurisdiction.
</div>
{% else %}
<p>
The references below carry their statutory citation. Treat them as a prompt to
confirm the controlling period with counsel — <strong>not</strong> as the
governing deadline for this matter.
</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>Limitation</th>
      <th>Period</th>
      <th>Citation</th>
      <th>Approx. runout</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for lc in ts.limitation_clocks %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ lc.ref.claim_kind | capitalize }}{% if lc.ref.illustrative %}<span class="secondary">example only</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ lc.ref.label }}{% if not lc.ref.verified %}<span class="secondary">unverified — confirm citation</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ lc.ref.period }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ lc.ref.citation }}</td>
      <td>
        {% if lc.approx_deadline %}
          ~{{ lc.approx_deadline }}
          {% if lc.status == "may_have_elapsed" %}<span class="secondary">may have elapsed — confirm tolling</span>
          {% elif lc.status == "approaching" %}<span class="secondary">{{ lc.approx_days_remaining }} day(s) left (approx)</span>
          {% else %}<span class="secondary">{{ lc.approx_days_remaining }} day(s) left (approx)</span>{% endif %}
        {% else %}
          <span class="secondary">{% if lc.ref.illustrative %}varies — see note{% else %}confirm with counsel{% endif %}</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p class="secondary">
Approximate runout dates assume the clock started on the incident date
({{ ts.incident_date or "unknown" }}). The true start date can differ — many
claims accrue on discovery, and statutory tolling can pause the clock. Counsel
confirms which period applies and the exact date.
</p>
{% for lc in ts.limitation_clocks %}
{% if lc.ref.note or lc.ref.accrual %}
<p style="font-size:.88em;margin:.4rem 0">
  <strong>{{ lc.ref.label }}</strong> ({{ lc.ref.citation }}):
  {% if lc.ref.accrual %}{{ lc.ref.accrual }} {% endif %}{{ lc.ref.note or "" }}
</p>
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

<h2>3. Recommended Next Step</h2>
<p>
Engage licensed counsel in {{ ts.jurisdiction_raw or "the relevant jurisdiction" }}
promptly to confirm the controlling limitation periods and preserve every
available claim, and — in parallel — pursue the time-critical exchange
freeze(s) above through law enforcement. The two clocks run independently;
acting early on both maximises the chance of recovery.
</p>

<p class="secondary" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
Recupero is an investigation firm, not a law firm, and provides no legal
representation. This advisory is general legal information compiled to help a
victim and their counsel avoid missing a deadline; it is not legal advice and
creates no attorney–client relationship. Do not rely on any period stated here
without confirmation from licensed counsel in the applicable jurisdiction.
</p>

</section>
</body>
</html>
